    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1031"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1031">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EAC1"
                    >EAC</gloss>/7–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1031<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract<note n="1" xml:id="d1031fn1">For the other
                            portions of this message, see <ref target="#d1037">document No.
                                1037</ref>.</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-24">24 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Tripartite Conference, Babelsberg, top secret from <persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName> serial number 44360. Sent the Secretary
                    Babelsberg top secret from <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName> and to
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> as 7434, July 24, <gloss
                        target="#t_Comea1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Comea</hi>
                    </gloss> 340.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss> met last night to complete two outstanding
                    documents. British informed U. S. they did not have full authority to accept
                    Soviet draft final paragraph for covering report to <gloss target="#t_EAC1"
                        >EAC</gloss> agreement amending agreement on zones occupation Germany.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d1031fn2">For <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>’
                        reply to this message, following a conversation at the Berlin Conference
                        between <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_SSW1">Strang</persName>, see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>,
                            <ref target="#pg_407">p. 407</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
